events.name: Google I/O Extended Buea 2017
events.description: It's That Time Of The Year Again When We Get Acquainted With Google's Latest Technologies And How We Can Apply Them To Our Startups, Academics And Communities For Faster Scale. There'll Be Code Labs On Google Cloud Platform, App Engine, Tensorflow, Kubernetes, AngularJS, Firebase And Google Analytics.

events.name: GDD Europe 2017 Extended Buea
events.description:
Google Developer Days (GDD) are global events showcasing the latest developer products and platforms from Google to help you quickly develop high quality apps, grow & retain an active user base, and tap into tools to earn more.

GDD Extended Buea Will Be An Event Where We LiveStream The Event and follow through with Codelabs on Tensorflow and GCP.

events.name: DevFest Fako 2017
events.description: The DevFest Fako 2017 event is a three-days-long hack-streak aimed at getting students, developers and entrepreneurs from GDGs in Fako (GDG Buea and GDG Limbe ) to learn Google's technologies such as Firebase, Cloud And Tensorflow and use them to build a PWA utilising Firebase Cloud and Offline-first functions. We intend to develop this PWA during a two-day Firebase AppFest at Skylabase Inc on Thursday November 9th And Friday November 10th 2017. The very next day, we'll showcase the PWA, Launch a Tensorflow Masterclass, promote gender diversity as well as enjoy a Fireside Chat on Cloud Computing at Eta Palace Hotel .

events.name: IWD Buea 2018
events.description:
It's an honor to be hosting the 2018 International Women's Day Celebration, a women's tech conference. This event will highlight the stories of our growing female community of designers, developers, and technology entrepreneurs.

International Women's Day (IWD) 2018 Buea is a hands-on driven event that aims at providing developers and tech enthusiasts (females especially) with fundamental skills in Android application development, Docker, Arduino and Graphic design while addressing the under-representation of women in STEM ( Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics).

This event will be characterized by a panel session, codelabs, inspiring videos, and lightning talks. Summarily, there will be four parallel codelab sessions, and each participant will have to register for just one session. Requirements:
Pen, Book, and Laptop

Event Agenda: https://goo.gl/b7k6Y9

events.name: Git/Github Workshop
events.description:
The Git/Github workshop class is geared towards teaching participants how to use version control systems (case study-Git and Github). It will be a hands-on practical session.

Requirements.
1. A laptop
2. An internet box
3. A notebook and pen

events.name: Google I/O Extended Buea 2018
events.description: The Google I/O Extended Buea 2018 event is a three-days-long event ( View Party, Hackday and Creative Day ) aimed at getting tech enthusiasts, students, developers and entrepreneurs from GDG Buea to learn and gain hand-on experience using Google's technologies such as Google Cloud Platform, Flutter, Firebase And Tensorflow as well as understand the critical place of UX/UI design in software development. During the View Party, we'll watch the Google I/O 2018 videos to learn what’s new in Android, Cloud, Tensorflow, Firebase and PWA. The Hackday will be a day where developers experience hands-on Codelab sessions on the aforementioned technologies while the Creative Day will be a day for the audience to learn the critical place of UI/UX design in software design at Eta Palace Hotel.

events.description: The DevFest Buea 2018 event is a two-days-long event ( 10:00 AM to 6:00 PM Each Day ) taking place at ActivSpaces Buea aimed at getting developers and entrepreneurs from the Buea tech community to learn about Google's technologies such as Firebase, GCP, Cloud Functions And Tensorflow as well as share their experiences contributing to open source. events.name: Google Summer of Code (GSoC) 2019 Mentorship

venue.name: ActivSpaces, 1st Trust Building Top Left Floor, Great Soppo

events.description:
Help us change the world one line of code at a time!

Over the last 14 years, GSoC has enabled more than 14,762 students from 109 countries to work with 651 open source projects and produce millions of lines of code since its inception in 2005.

The goals of the program are to:
● Motivate students to begin participating in open source
development.
● Provide students in Computer Science and related fields the
opportunity to do work related to their academic pursuits.
● Give students exposure to real-world software development
scenarios (e.g., testing, version control, software licensing,
mailing-list etiquette, etc.).
● Create more open source code.
● Help open source projects bring in new developers.

* Event Agenda: https://goo.gl/reqCuu

* Things to bring:
- A laptop
- A wifi box
- Positive attitude.

* Useful resources:
- GSOC timeline: https://goo.gl/aMEMFm
- Program overview: https://goo.gl/bY9UGf
- Student guide: https://goo.gl/re9xTv

events.name: Cloud Study Jam

venue.name: ActivSpaces, 1st Trust Building Top Left Floor, Great Soppo

events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want.

SOME TOPICS THAT WILL BE COVERED:
1. Firebase web: Learn how to use Firebase for web application deployment by developing a chat client web application that utilizes Firebase's core features.

2. Running WordPress on App Engine Flexible Environment

3. Extract, Analyze, and Translate Text from Images with the Cloud ML APIs

NB: Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.
events.how_to_find_us: For any further inquiries, please contact +237 679574561 or info@gdgbuea.net

events.name: TensorFlow 2.0 Global Doc Sprint Buea
events.description:
TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning library for research and production. TensorFlow offers APIs for beginners and experts to develop for desktop, mobile, web, and cloud.

TensorFlow 2.0 is a major release focused on ease of use and clarity while maintains its flexibility.

Are you interested in learning about what is new with TensorFlow 2.0?
Would you like to contribute to TensorFlow 2.0 and learn the PR and review process? You can get started by improving its documentation.

Join the pilot of the global docs sprint at GDG Buea, where you'll learn how to review and create pull requests for making changes to TensorFlow documentation.

Target audience: ideally you know Machine Learning, TensorFlow or Python but it's not a pre-requisite in order to contribute to TensorFlow docs.

Things to bring/setup
1. Your own laptop
2. An internet box (optional)
3. Have a GitHub account

Agenda:
http://bit.ly/2K1Ao5e
